'''Natural capitalism{{w|Natural capitalism}}''' (described in a book of the same name by [[Paul Hawken]]{{w|Paul Hawken}}, [[Amory Lovins]]{{w|Amory Lovins}} and [[Hunter Lovins]]{{w|Hunter Lovins}} refers to an approach to using [[capitalism]] and market systems to encourage [[sustainability]]. It also has a focus on mimicking ecology ([[biomimicry]]) and moving towards a more strictly [[service economy]].

